Sec. 38.09.900.   Definitions.
In this chapter,
(1) brush means to clear a swath along the boundary lines of a homestead entry so that the boundary lines may be identified from the ground;
(2) commissioner means the commissioner of natural resources;
(3) resident means an individual who has resided in the state for one year, is a U.S. citizen and does not claim residence in another state, and shows by all attending circumstances an intent to make this state the individual's permanent residence.
